The individual is of primary importance. Society is composed of individuale, and their spirit is its spirit. This is not to say that the individual is of exclusive importance, or that we are not to take full account of the dependence of character on social cir· cumstances. It does not mean that we are Individ- ualists; that we sever the individual from society, or absorb society in the individual, or oppose the individual to society.
